Ohio Nonviolence Week is October 4-10, 2020, and Youngstown City School District is hosting its annual Poetry and Art Contests. The purpose of Nonviolence Week is to promote peace in our local, national, and global community.

Poems and artwork must be turned in by September 18, 2020, at 4 p.m. to be eligible for prizes.

For more information about the qualifications of the poetry and art contests and brainstorming ideas, check out the fact sheets below!

What do "you" do when one of your students has a traumatic experience? "You" reach out for help! I'm thankful that William Burney, of CIRV grabbed ahold and pushed forward. School starts soon and we needed one of our Wilson scholars focused and we needed to uplift his mom. Thank you to our Mayor Jamael Tito Brown for participating in a surprise parade for him, and gifting him with a key to the city. He was in complete shock when YPD and YFD showed up in a cruiser, motorcycles, and a fire truck with sirens and flashing lights. You all our amazing and have big hearts.

My Wilson Family never disappoints! Shout to our awesome leader, Rick Fox who gave us the green light to organize this. ‚Ä¶

To continue to support families and scholars in developing early literacy skills, the YCSD's Early Childhood Program purchased Summer Reading Kits and Workbooks for 2019 - 2020 YCSD preschool scholars. Some teachers chose to deliver the kits to their scholars while the rest were mailed to the homes. If a 2019-20 YCSD preschool family has not received a reading kit by July 20, they should reach out to Preschool Supervisor Melissa.puhalla@youngstown.k12.oh.us.

On June 27, Mrs. Cooper delivered her books and captured some adorable photos .
#YCSDFamily

post_text:
Our weekly food distribution will continue tomorrow from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at our same sites: McGuffey, Volney, Harding, Paul C. Bunn, Taft and Williamson elementary schools; the former Princeton Junior High and East High School.

The weekly distribution will include boxes of fresh fruits and vegetables for families.

There is a limited number of the boxes and they will be distributed one per vehicle, first come, first served.

Our weekly food distribution will continue through July.

post_text:
YCSD's food distribution continues tomorrow (Monday, June 8) at the same eight sites: Volney, McGuffey, Paul C. Bunn, Harding, Taft and Williamson elementary schools; the former Princeton Junior High; and East High School.

Beginning tomorrow, boxes of fresh fruits and vegetables will be given out during distribution at all of the sites. There is a limited number of the boxes and they will be given one per vehicle, first come, first served.

The 11-pound boxes contain celery, apples, oranges, potatoes, onions and other items, subject to availability. It‚Äôs a program of the United States Department of Agriculture to ensure people have access to fresh food during the pandemic.

USDA is partnering with farmers and food distributors for the program.

Distribution will be from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. #YCSDFamily

This book is a sequel to "The Kissing Hand," which was read to us yesterday, May 19, by Maria Pappas. Our CEO Justin M. shared_text:

May 19 at 8:13 AM ¬∑

We are in the final week of highlighting our senior labs with a ‚ÄòSenior Lab Spotlight' üåü

Each spotlight includes a special message from our #ChoffinCTC instructors since they aren't able to end the school year with their seniors in person.

Today's spotlight is on our Biotechnology senior lab. In this program, students conducted hands-on activities in anatomy and physiology, forensic science, cell biology, disease research, immunology, organic chemistry, medical technology, environmental science, and genetic engineering.

Congratulations Biotechnology seniors üéì #Classof2020 #ChoffinProud #WeMissYou #SeniorStrong

shared_text:
Choffin Career & Technical Center
May 13 at 8:10 AM ¬∑

Over the next few weeks leading up to graduation, we will be highlighting our senior labs with a ‚ÄòSenior Lab Spotlight' üåü

Each spotlight includes a special message from our #ChoffinCTC instructors since they aren't able to end the school year with their seniors in person.

Today's spotlight is on our Welding senior lab. In this program, our seniors learned how to manipulate the power of fire and electricity to design and construct the metal products people use every day. Our welding students operate the same advanced welding and fabrication equipment used by professionals to manipulate metal for artistic and industrial applications.

Congratulations Welding seniors üéì #Classof2020 #ChoffinProud #WeMissYou #SeniorStrong
